  {
   "uuid": "1da58856-435b-429d-a925-3b73656d3250",
   "title": "The Woman in Cabin 10",
   "year": 2025,
   "runtimeMin": 96,
   "viewings": [
    "2025-11-10 20:46:15"
   ],
   "rewatchCount": 0,
   "status": "watched",
   "score": 8.5,
   "emotions": [
    {
     "id": "28",
     "label": "Отлично",
     "emoji": "😍",
     "score": 8.5
    }
   ],
   "favorite": false,
   "lists": [],
   "review": "It's so funny to see how movies are made for the sake of the agenda.\n\nThe cover features a detective story about a murder on a yacht, similar to Agatha Christie's \"Death on the Nile.\" It looks promising, considering my love for detective stories.\n\nWhat did we get in the end? What lesson did the movie teach us? Here's what I found:\n\n1. All girls (white and black) are intelligent, decent, kind, and compassionate. All positive, in general.\n2. All white men (there were 6-7 of them) are two-faced, greedy rats + terrans who keep their women in fear and beat them. All negative.\n3. The only black man among all the white men is a hero who is willing to sacrifice himself for his ex. A positive character.\n\nEither this was the intention, or the actors were poorly chosen for their roles, although they are well-known and play well.",
   "addedAt": "2025-11-10 20:46:15"
  },
